魭字的基本解释

魭
yuán
古同“鼋”。

魭字的汉语字典释义

[①]［yuán］
［《集韻》愚袁切，平元，疑。］
(1)鱼名。
(2)同“黿”。
[②]［wǎn］
［《集韻》五换切，去换，疑。］
［《廣韻》五官切，上緩，疑。］
见“魭2斷”。

魭字的康熙字典解释

【亥集中】【魚字部】　魭； 康熙笔画：15； 页码：页1466第21
【集韻】愚袁切，音元。與黿同。大鼈也。【本草】如鼈而大。又【集韻】五管切，音浣。輐或作魭。魭斷，無圭角貌。【莊子·天下篇】而不免於魭斷。【註】雖立，而魭斷無圭角也。又【集韻】【正韻】?五換切，音玩。義同。

Kangxi dictionary interpretation of words
[Hai Collection] [Fish Character Department] 　魭; Kangxi Strokes: 15; Page Number: Page 1466 No. 21
[Ji Yun] Yu Yuan cut, phonemes. Same as Yuan. The big turtle is also. 【Materia Medica】It is as big as a turtle. Also 【Jiyun】Five-pipe cutting, sound huan.輐 or make 魭. It is broken, and there is no corner appearance. 【Zhuangzi·Tianxia】Inevitably break. 【Note】Although it is standing, there are no corners for it. Also 【Ji Yun】【Zheng Yun】? Five change cuts, sound play. The same meaning.
